comment: Global offset is -1.4 to compensate glass-supported homing procedure. GelMA (T1) and HAMA (T2). Vol. T1: 600 µL (layer 1), + 600 µL (layer 3). Vol. T2: 600 µL (layer 2).  Washing channels: dipping, then rinsing 5x0.6 mL warm DPBS with pipette, removing excess liquid with KimWipe (touching channels). Store in warm ECGM2 until further use.  Perfect prints except one with air bubble in first layer (but on edge) --> position 6.  Transferring all at the same time into separate 24-wells with 0.5 mL 2x Hase in ECGM2 +P/S (230204 MF).     Note: no cells in GelMA, HUVECS and MSCs are mixed in equal parts into HAMA
